==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emerge
<hw>E*merge"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Emerged</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Emerging</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>emergere</ets>, <ets>emersum</ets>; <ets>e</ets> out +
<ets>mergere</ets> to dip, plunge. See <er>Merge</er>.]</ety> <def>To
rise out of a fluid; to come forth from that in which anything has been
plunged, enveloped, or concealed; to issue and appear; <as>as, to
<ex>emerge</ex> from the water or the ocean; the sun <ex>emerges</ex>
from behind the moon in an eclipse; to <ex>emerge</ex> from poverty or
obscurity.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧Thetis . . . <xex>emerging</xex> from the
deep.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those who have <qex>emerged</qex> from very low, some from the
lowest, classes of society.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emergence</ent>⟦br⟧
